verbose_text: It is reasonable to assume that the R-to-H mutation at the 372nd position (R69H) together with the D-to-N mutation at the 369th position (D66N), which enhanced antiviral activity of TRIMCyp against HIV-2 but diminished anti-HIV-1 activity, arose early in a macaque common ancestor.
evidence: R-to-H mutation at the 372nd position (R69H) together with the D-to-N mutation at the 369th position (D66N), which enhanced antiviral activity of TRIMCyp
